&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Close the Care Gap: Everyone Deserves Access To Cancer Care&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The theme for the 2022-2024 period is &amp;quot;Close the Care Gap: Everyone Deserves Access To Cancer Care&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World Cancer Day&lt;/strong&gt; is observed globally on&lt;strong&gt; February 4&lt;/strong&gt; each year to raise awareness about cancer, its prevention, and the importance of early detection.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Th&lt;strong&gt;e theme for the 2022-2024&lt;/strong&gt; period is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Close the Care Gap: Everyone Deserves Access To Cancer Care&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; highlighting the need for global collaboration in the fight against cancer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sub-theme, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Together, we challenge those in power,&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; emphasises accountability from leaders to allocate essential resources for eradicating cancer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World Cancer Day&lt;/strong&gt; dates back to the&lt;strong&gt; World Summit Against Cancer&lt;/strong&gt; in&lt;strong&gt; Paris&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;1999&lt;/strong&gt;, where the concept was proposed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; Charter of Paris Against Cancer&lt;/strong&gt; was signed on &lt;strong&gt;February 4, 2000&lt;/strong&gt;, during the follow-up World Summit, officially marking the first observance of World Cancer Day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;World Cancer Day holds significance in increasing awareness about early detection to reduce cancer-related fatalities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In 2020, cancer became the leading cause of global deaths, with approximately 10 million fatalities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Landsteiner&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ABO grouping of blood was discovered in 1901 by Karl Landsteiner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Based on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;presence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;absence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antigens&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;on the RBCs namely A and B, blood grouping is done.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Karl Landsteiner&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;at the University of Vienna discovered why some blood transfusions were successful while others could be deadly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Landsteiner discovered the ABO blood group system by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;mixing the red cells and serum of each of his staff&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Blood Groups and Donor Compatibility&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41); width: 350px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Blood Group&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Antigens on RBCs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Antibodies in Plasma&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Donor&amp;rsquo;s Group&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;A&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;anti-B&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;A, O&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;B&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;anti-A&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;B, O&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; A, B&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;nil&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;AB, A, B, O&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;O&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;nil&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;anti-A, B&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;
			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;O&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;128 bits&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The full form of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IPv6&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Internet Protocol Version 6&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IPv6&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is referred to as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;numeric label&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is mainly used for&amp;nbsp;recognising&amp;nbsp;and locating a network interface of a computer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The packet header of&amp;nbsp;IPv6 holds the IP addresses which is used for identifying&amp;nbsp;the source and the destination of each packet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IPv6&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is known as&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;successor&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Internet Protocol version 4 (IPv4)&lt;/span&gt;. The IPv4 was the first addressing infrastructure of the Internet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The value of the IP address of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IPv4&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;32-bit&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;whereas the value of the IP address of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;IPv6&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;128 bits&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/02/Screenshot%202023-02-02%20at%202.14.53%20PM.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 280px; height: 135px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Thus the&amp;nbsp;correct answer is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;128 bits&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anaimudi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Anaimudi is located in the Western Ghats mountain range in the Indian state of Kerala.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It has an elevation of 2,695 meters (8,842 feet) above sea level.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Anaimudi is a popular trekking destination and is known for its scenic beauty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The peak offers stunning views of the surrounding mountains, valleys, and forests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Doddabetta&lt;/strong&gt; is the highest peak in the &lt;strong&gt;Nilgiri Hills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Jindhagada&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the highest peak in the &lt;strong&gt;Eastern Ghats.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Udagamandalam (Ooty)&lt;/strong&gt; is a hill station in the &lt;strong&gt;Nilgiri Hills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mahanadi&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Western Ghats&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp; also called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Sahyadri&lt;/span&gt;, north-south running range of mountains or hills in western India that for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the crest&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;western edge&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Deccan plateau&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;parallel to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Malabar coast of the Arabian sea&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The major rivers&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;originating in the western ghat are the following
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Godavari&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;India&amp;#39;s second longest river&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;after&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the Ganga&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the third largest in India&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;drains about 10%&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;India&amp;#39;s total geographical area&lt;/span&gt;. Its source is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Trimbakeswar, Nashik, Maharashtra.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Cauvery&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is one of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;major Indian rivers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;flowing through&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Karnataka and Tamil Nadu states&lt;/span&gt;. In ancient&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Tamil Literature&lt;/span&gt;, the river was also called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Ponni.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Tungabhadra River&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is a river that starts&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;flowing through&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;state of Karnataka&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;during&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;most of its course&lt;/span&gt;. before flowing along the border between&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Telangana, and Andhra Pradesh&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ultimately joining the Krishna River near Gundimalla village&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Jolumba Godwal district of Telangana&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Mahanadi&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is a major river in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;East Central India&lt;/span&gt;. it drains an area of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;around 132,100 kilometres&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and has a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;total length of 900 kilometres&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Mahanadi&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is also known for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hirakud dam&lt;/span&gt;. The river flows through the states of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chattisgarh and Odisha&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and finally merged with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bay of Bengal&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Which of the following is the correct match of the column-A with column-B?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;width:330px;&quot; width=&quot;330&quot;&gt;
